[4/30] P5 English EOY Raffles 2025 — Q7  Primary 5  (12.5s)
============================================================
STEM: Jane, together with her cousins, ___ at the theme park last week.
  (1) is
  (2) are
  (3) was
  (4) were
ANSWER: 3

ELABORATION (630 chars):
This question tests **subject-verb agreement** and **past tense**.

The main subject is "Jane", which is a singular noun. The phrase "together with her cousins" is extra information that does not make the subject plural, so we need a singular, past tense verb because of the time clue "last week". Therefore, **(3)** **was** is correct!

Here is why the other options fail:
**(1)** fails because **is** uses the wrong tense (**present tense**).
**(2)** fails because **are** uses the wrong tense and is a mismatched subject (**plural**).
**(4)** fails because **were** is a mismatched subject (**plural**) for the singular "Jane".

