[6/30] P5 English EOY Raffles 2025 — Q9  Primary 5  (13.5s)
============================================================
STEM: My mother is the person ___ opinion I value the most so I would always go to her for advice.
  (1) who
  (2) which
  (3) whom
  (4) whose
ANSWER: 4

ELABORATION (658 chars):
This question tests your knowledge of **relative pronouns** used to show possession.

Option **(4)** is correct because **whose** shows that the "opinion" belongs to "the person" (your mother). We use the possessive pronoun **whose** to link a person to something they own or give.

Here is why the other options are incorrect:
- Option **(1)** is a subject pronoun error; **who** is used for a person doing an action, not to show ownership.
- Option **(2)** is a mismatched pronoun error; **which** is used for things or animals, not people.
- Option **(3)** is an object pronoun error; **whom** is used for a person receiving an action, not for possession.

